<FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="2">

	
	



	
	
		
	



It has emerged that of the hundreds of people arrested before and after England's game against Germany, one Englishman has been charged and is due to appear in a Charleroi court.
<P>
The man is described as being in his early 20s and he is accused of assaulting a policeman on Saturday.
<P>
Of the 300 people detained in Brussels last weekend, two Englishmen will face criminal charges in court later this week. 
<P>
A senior Belgian police officer, Assistant Commissioner Christian de Coninck, said: "I am sure there were no innocent bystanders arrested.
<P>
"When there are clashes going on, normal people run away or take cover, they don't stand there provoking the police and throwing bottles and cans at them."
<P>


